rmeneutic framing for analyzing representations of death across American literature and media.  afunded by Swiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aAmerica. 4aCultural Studies. 4aFilm. 4aLiterature. 4aMedia. 4aPopular Culture. 4aTelevision. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAmerica.  aCultural Studies.  aFilm.  aLiterature.  aMedia.  aPopular Culture.  aTelevision.2 aSwiss National Science Foundation (SNSF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839465691?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839465691zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839465691/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA